<TITLE> Top 20 player purchases so far at IPL auction </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MUMBAI, India, Feb 20 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Following are the 20 most expensive players purchased so far by the Indian Premier League's eight franchises at an ongoing auction on Wednesday. The team will pay the winning bid to the player annually. The contracts are for a three-year period and are guarenteed by the Indian cricket board. The inaugural 44-day, Twenty20 tournament gets underway on April 18. India's one-day captain Mahendra Dhoni is the costliest player so far at $1.5 million per year. 1. Mahendra Dhoni (India) $1.5m to Chennai 2. Andrew Symonds (Australia) $1.35m to Hyderabad 3. Sanath Jayasuriya (Sri Lanka) $975,000 to Mumbai 4. Brett Lee (Australia) $900,000 to Mohali 4. Jacques Kallis (South Africa) $900,000 to Bangalore 6. Harbhajan Singh (India) $850,000 to Mumbai 7. Chris Gayle (West Indies) $800,000 to Kolkata 8. Brendon McCullum (New Zealand) $700,000 to Kolkata 8. Kumar Sangakkara (Sri Lanka) $700,000 to Mohali 8. Adam Gilchrist (Australia) $700,000 to Hyderabad 11. Shahid Afridi (Pakistan) $675,000 to Hyderabad 11. Jacob Oram (New Zealand) $675,000 to Chennai 13. Mohammad Asif (Pakistan) $650,000 to Delhi 14. S.Sreesanth (India) $625,000 to Mohali 14. Daniel Vettori (New Zealand) $625,000 to Delhi 16. Muttiah Muralitharan (Sri Lanka) $600,000 to Chennai 17. Herschelle Gibbs (South Africa) $575,000 to Hyderabad 18. Anil Kumble (India) $500,000 to Bangalore 18. Shoaib Malik (Pakistan) $500,000 to Delhi 20. Mahela Jayawardene (Sri Lanka) $475,000 to Mohali 20. Graeme Smith (South Africa) $475,000 to Jaipu
